Gymshark Train
We train. We motivate. We grow. Together.
Step up your game and join the family, so we can #GymsharkTrain together 🦈

#Gymsharktrain

#Gymsharktrain

#Gymsharktrain

node.text:
Get ready to make that full body work with this powerful at-home HIIT workout from @mrandmrsmuscle 💪 
Tag a friend who you would duo this with!
#Gymsharktrain

Please only take part in the workout if you are medically and physically fit and have not been advised not to participate by a qualified medical professional. If your health or fitness changes adversely in any way before, during and/or after the workout please seek and follow medical advice without delay.

node.text:
@wozldn brings you a 🔥 full body workout to celebrate the last day of #Gymshark66! Expect 30 minutes of dynamic and energetic H.I.I.T exercises – you're defo going to need some water 🥵

Please only take part in the workout if you are medically and physically fit and have not been advised not to participate by a qualified medical professional. If your health or fitness changes adversely in any way before, during and/or after the workout please seek and follow medical advice without delay.

Want to increase your flexibility? Then try this mobility flow routine by @jessicaolie 🙌
Click the link in our bio for more mobility workouts‼️ #Gymsharktrain

node.text:
If August is your month to get back into the gym, arrive prepared and ready to smash it with this guided workout from @yandz_x 🦈
1️⃣ Kneeling thruster (3x8-10)
2️⃣ Weighted push up (3x8-10)
3️⃣ Plate swing squat (3x8-10)
4️⃣ Plate hold bicycle (3x8-10)
Don't forget to tap save ✔️
#Gymsharktrain

Pay your calves the attention they deserve with this dedicated @fraserwilsonfit calf workout 🦵
Swipe, save and go:
✖️ Standing calf raise (4x5)
✖️ Barbell squat (6x8)
✖️ Backwards lunge (3x16)
✖️ Single leg step down (3x15)
✖️ Leg extensions (3x10-15)
Tap the link in bio for workouts that you can play, pause and jump back into when you're ready ▶️
#Gymsharktrain

node.text:
12 min full body workout: Modified vs. Advanced 🔥 
Pick your tempo and following along with @lisafiitt:
1️⃣ High Knees
2️⃣ Squat with jump
3️⃣ Scissor step with jab
4️⃣ Star jump into Burpee
Warm up with star jumps. Compete each exercise for a non-stop round of 5 mins followed by a 2 min rest. Then repeat for another 5 mins. Remember to cool down and stretch afterwards ✅
Tag your training partner for your next studio session 👫
⁣#Gymsharktrain

node.text:
LEGS with a focus on QUADS 🦵
Follow along with @_brittanylupton:
1️⃣ Squats (6 sets)
2️⃣ Reverse lunges superset with (4x10)
3️⃣ Heels elevated front squat (4x10)
4️⃣ Leg press (4x10)
Hit save + check out the link in our bio, so you can plan your week of workouts in our Training app ✅
#Gymsharktrain

Start your week strong with this #fullbodyworkout from @theqii_tofitness! 💥
Try it for yourself ⬇️
1️⃣ ⁣Split squat⁣⁣ (5x12)
2️⃣ Barbell boat push⁣⁣ (5x12)
3️⃣ Military press⁣⁣ (5x12)
4️⃣ Barbell kicks ⁣⁣(5x12)
5️⃣ Barbell row⁣⁣ (5x12)
#Gymsharktrain

Build strength and muscle with with these all round upper body exercises + additional full body workout 🏋️‍♀️
Hit save to try it for yourself!
1️⃣ Single arm cable pull down (tempo 3211) 
into...
2️⃣ Press ups (4x10-15)
3️⃣ Dumbbell standing press (4x8)
4️⃣ Dumbbell lateral raise (4x12)
5️⃣ Chin ups (8x5)
6️⃣ Dips (8x5)
7️⃣ Slams (12x5)
📹: @lucydavis_fit
#Gymsharktrain

If you're ready to make some serious change, give this focused @realrubaali workout a go!
💥 Dumbbell lunge
💥 Burpee with Star jump
💥 Leg raise with Overhead press
💥 Squat jump with Arnold press
💥 One-sided elevated push-up
12-15 reps per side | 4 sets | 30 sec rest after each set
Tag a friend to motivate their next workout 👇
#Gymsharktrain
